<BlogCrossLinks current={slug} />

<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Using All 5 Vowels — A, E, I, O, U Words for Scrabble</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Drawing a rack full of vowels feels terrible — until you know the words that use all five. SEQUOIA, EULOGIA, and ADIEU turn a seemingly unplayable hand into legitimate scoring opportunities. These all-five-vowel words are your emergency toolkit for vowel-heavy racks.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">All-5-Vowel Words by Length</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
    <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
      <tr>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Word</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Points</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Length</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">SEQUOIA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Bingo + Q without U-after</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">OUIJA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">J(8) makes it worth it</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">EULOGIA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Bingo candidate</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">MIAOUED</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Past tense of miaou</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">ADIEU</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Shortest common option</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">AUDIO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4 vowels + D</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">ABOITEAU</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3">8-letter bingo</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The SEQUOIA Strategy</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Best All-Vowel Word</div>
  <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">SEQUOIA</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">16 pts base · 7 letters · 50 pt bingo bonus · Uses Q without requiring U-after</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">SEQUOIA uses all 5 vowels plus Q and S. It's the holy grail of vowel-dump bingo words — scoring 66 total points (16 base + 50 bingo) while clearing your entire rack of excess vowels.</p>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">When to Use These Words</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">5+ vowels on rack:</span> If you draw 5 or more vowels, don't exchange. Look for ADIEU, AUDIO, or longer all-vowel words first. Exchanging wastes a turn; playing dumps vowels AND scores.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Q with vowels:</span> If you have Q plus multiple vowels, SEQUOIA might be playable. Even if you can't bingo, the Q alone is worth 10 points and you clear 5 vowels in one move.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack balance matters:</span> Even playing ADIEU for just 6 points is better than exchanging — you score AND clear 4 vowels, refilling with (hopefully) more consonants from the bag.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">More Multi-Vowel Words (4+ Vowels)</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SEQUOIA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OUIJA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADIEU</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AUDIO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">IAMBI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AQUAE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">URAEI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LOOIE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Rack Balance Rule</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The ideal Scrabble rack has <span class="text-white font-medium">3-4 vowels and 3-4 consonants</span>. If you draw 5+ vowels, playing an all-vowel word brings you back to balance without wasting a turn on exchange. Even 6 points is better than zero.</p>
